{"topicSections":[{"title":"Structures","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSBulletList\/Item"],"anchor":"Structures"},{"title":"Initializers","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSBulletList\/init(type:textStyle:isBold:items:)"],"anchor":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSBulletList\/body"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties"},{"title":"Enumerations","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSBulletList\/TextStyle","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSBulletList\/Type","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSBulletList\/UnorderedAsset"],"anchor":"Enumerations"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSBulletList\/View-Implementations","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSBulletList\/View-Implementations"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Default-Implementations","title":"Default Implementations"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"],"type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSBulletList"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/ContentDisplay"]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Types","anchor":"Types"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Three types are proposed:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Unordered (by default)","type":"text"}]},{"text":": Collects related items that don’t need to be in a specific order or sequence.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ordered"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Collects related items with numeric order or sequence."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Bare"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": An unordered list without any bullets or alphanumeric sequence."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Types can be mixed in list, but must be identical for the same "},{"code":"OUDSBulletList.NestedLevel","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Levels","level":2,"text":"Levels"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Lists can include nested items to indicate hierarchy or subcategories, with indentation distinguishing each level."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Arrange ordered list items logically, such as ranking by importance, highest to lowest values, or in alphabetical \/ numeric order."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Three levels are maximum."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Text-Style","text":"Text Style","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"List can be used with different font sizes:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Body Large","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": If the text accompanying the list component is the Body Large text. This variant is designed for more visual, engaging experiences."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Body Medium","type":"text"}]},{"text":": If the text accompanying the list component is the Body Medium text. This variant is best suited for functional, task-oriented experiences.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"anchor":"Cases-forbidden-by-design","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Cases forbidden by design"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"it is not allowed to have a depth of items greater than 3"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Internationalisation-considerations","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Internationalisation considerations"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For latin-based speaking countries, like France, Spain, United Kingdom or Belgium, the european “arabic” numbers are used for the first level of depth"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the ordered bullet list. For the second and third levels, the european alphabets are used with upper and lower case values."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"However for countries speaking arabic, these rules can’t be applied. Indeed, there is no notion of upper and lower case characters in arabic alphabet."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In addition, the numbers in use (i.e. the european “arabic” numbers like “1, 2, 3”) are accepted in arabic countries, even if the “true arabic” numbers (like “ ٢ ٣ ١”) are used"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in middle-east arabic countries and for official documents."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Thus the OUDS ordered bullet list will use “european” numbers for first level, and arabic alphabets for second and third levels."}]},{"anchor":"Code-samples","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Code samples"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["       \/\/ 1. Unordered list with bullets","       OUDSBulletList {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }","","       \/\/ 1.1. Item of Unordered list with bullet as tick, a text style","       \/\/ body medium and text bold","       OUDSBulletList(type: .unordered(asset: .tick),","                      textStyle: .bodyMedium,","                      isBold: true)  {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }","","       \/\/ 2. Bare list with 3 items","       OUDSBulletList(type: .bare) {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }","","       \/\/ 3. Ordered list with 3 items","       OUDSBulletList(type: .ordered) {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }","","       \/\/ 3.1. Ordered list with 3 items in first level,","       \/\/ and one item as sub item (second level),","       \/\/ and 2 items as sub item in (third level)","       OUDSBulletList(type: .ordered) {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\") {","               OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1\") {","                   OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1.1\")","                   OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1.2\")","               }","           }","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }","","       \/\/ Same Bullet list but items in third level with free icon as bullet","       let icon = Image(decorative: \"ic_heart\")","       OUDSBulletList(type: .ordered) {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\") {","               OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1\", subListType: .unordered(asset: .icon(icon))) {","                   OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1.1\")","                   OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1.2\")","               }","           }","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }"]},{"anchor":"Rich-text-recommendations","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Rich text recommendations"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Rich text can be applied for bullet list whatever the "},{"code":"isBold","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" flag is."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Strong text can be used sparingly within alert messages to highlight key information."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Underlined text must not be used for emphasis, as it is commonly associated with links."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Underlined links must be bold."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If a hyperlink is needed within the content, the underlined style should be used."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Italic should be used with care, some brands do not allow it like Orange brand."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"No other text styles should be used."}]},{"anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Accessibility considerations"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Always check the results of rich text mode with high contrast, light and dark modes, and Voice Over vocalization."}]},{"anchor":"Design-documentation","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Design documentation"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-bullet-list"}]},{"anchor":"Themes-rendering","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Themes rendering"},{"anchor":"Orange","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Orange"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_bullet_list_Orange"}]},{"anchor":"Orange-Compact","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Orange Compact"},{"type":"paragr